CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1956, pg. 3, reads: "$10,000 Damage - While she was away fishing at Ackerman's Lake, there was almost as much water poured into the home of Mrs. Annie Leaks at 512 Protectory Place (rear) as there in Ackerman's Lake. A tremendously smoky, smouldering fire which broke out in cellar from unknown causes completely gutted the house and burned most of her household furnishings. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women, possibly including Annie Leaks, sorting through household debris, including mattresses and springs, outside of burned row house at 512 Protectory Place, Hill District
